creator: ResidentAgent.sg Pte Ltd
descriptionHtml:
This mobile app (free) is Singapore’s first home-grown E NoticeBoard, made available to residents of 5,000 individual estates.

It is not the “standard” kind of social networking mobile apps found on the App Store or Google Play. It is built based on a simple and cost-effective business model where your home estate is transformed into marketplace for basic services. This model is proven to be sustainable since 2006 with which, the following five Singapore’s first home-grown platforms are created:

1st - Estate-Services-Marketplace;
2nd - Estate-Services-Industry-Platform;
3rd - Estate-Services-Entrepreneur-Incubator;
4th - Estate-Social-Media Platform
5th - Estate-Sharing-Economy;

With 120 types of services available to be offered in 5,000 estates HDB/landed/private apartments), a total of 600,000 jobs will be created in Singapore. Collectively, they are expected to contribute $18 billion every year and add extra 3.52% growth per year on average to the Singapore GDP in the period 2020–2022.

We will now move from a Product-leading-Services modus operandi into a new Services-Led era. Accidentally, a brand-new market structure has been created
that is a hybrid of Monopoly and Monopolistic Competition. I call it EstateEconomy™ Business Model – where money can be made in your home estate!™

Read more about this business model on a 248-page paperback book written by David Lim – “Why Aren’t You Having Afternoon Naps?”.

If you are residing in Singapore, you can purchase this book through this mobile app (Book Price: S$32.00/Delivery Charges: S$4.00).

If you are residing outside of Singapore, please contact the publisher @ book@ResidentButler.sg for postage charges for different countries (Book Price: S$42.00).

creator: ResidentAgent.sg Pte Ltd
descriptionHtml:
Resident NoticeBoard™ - TackIt® is Singapore’s first home-grown E NoticeBoard mobile app made available to residents of 5,000 home estates.

It is not the “standard” kind of social networking mobile apps. It is built based on a simple
and cost-effective business model where each home estate is transformed into marketplace for
basic services. This model is proven to be sustainable by the founder/Author David Lim who
has been doing business in his small home estate of 700 units since 2006, up-to-date (as per
his book “Why Aren’t You Having Afternoon Naps?” available for sale @ Kinokunia, Popular
and Times bookstores in Singapore).
Embedded in this app are three business models of a new kind in the new normal, post-covid
economy. These include:

a) MiniMall® - Retail
- Where online meets 5,000 offline SalesReps in Singapore’s 5,000 home estates!
b) ResidentAgent® - Real Estate
- Where online meets 5,000 offline Salespersons, in Singapore’s 5,000 home estates!
c) ResidentButler® - Home-based
- Where online meets offline, in Singapore’s 5,000 home estates!

Together, a total of 134 positions are created in EVERY home estate - consisting of service
providers and sales representatives. In 5,000 home estates in Singapore, a total of 670,000
jobs are expected to be created.

This will make Resident NoticeBoard™ mobile app a brand-new marketplace platform and ecosystem for all service providers and sales representatives to thrive and grow together.

descriptionHtml:
This app is now available for free download in Indonesia, Malaysia and Singapore! It is the first E NoticeBoard app for Indonesia’s 273,000 home estates, Malaysia’s 32,000 home estates and Singapore’s 5,000 home estates.

Connecting Neighbours™ is the tagline of this app. However, it is more than a kampung spirit social media platform. It is in fact an Estate-Services-Marketplace created for everyone to do business in his/her home estate.

This is based on a simple and cost-effective business model created by the founder David Lim. He has been doing business in his small home estate of 700 units in Singapore since 2006! He has shared his experience in his book “Why Aren’t You Having Afternoon Naps?” published in May 2019. With Work From Home (WFH) being the new norm, every home estate has become an even BIGGER marketplace for services. Download the app to follow his blog on how he earns money from his home estate.

As a user, you can connect with:
(1) neighbours in your home estate;
(2) residents living in your country;
(3) residents living in all three countries through our E-Commerce Enabler MiniMall®. It is a marketplace of a total population of 310 million people in a combined 310,000 home estates in Indonesia, Malaysia and Singapore.

descriptionHtml:
This app is now available for free download in Indonesia, Malaysia and Singapore! It is the first E NoticeBoard app for Indonesia’s 273,000 home estates, Malaysia’s 32,000 home estates and Singapore’s 5,000 home estates.

Connecting Neighbours™ is the tagline of this app. However, it is more than a kampung spirit social media platform. It is in fact an Estate-Services-Marketplace created for everyone to do business in his/her home estate.

This is based on a simple and cost-effective business model created by the founder David Lim. He has been doing business in his small home estate of 700 units in Singapore since 2006! He has shared his experience in his book “Why Aren’t You Having Afternoon Naps?” published in May 2019. With Work From Home (WFH) being the new norm, every home estate has become an even BIGGER marketplace for services. Download the app to follow his blog on how he earns money from his home estate.

As a user, you can connect with:
(1) neighbours in your home estate;
(2) residents living in your country;
(3) residents living in all three countries through our E-Commerce Enabler MiniMall®. It is a marketplace of a total population of 310 million people in a combined 310,000 home estates in Indonesia, Malaysia and Singapore.
